Gold for Immediate Delivery Advances to Record

-- B y   K y o u n g w h a   K i m
-- 
2011-04-21T01:28:07Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-21/gold-gains-to-record-for-sixth-straight-day-climbs-to-1-506-32-per-ounce.html
(Corrects date since record run began.)  Gold for immediate delivery climbed
as much as 0.3 percent to an all-time high of $1,506.32 an ounce
in  Singapore  today. The metal has risen to a record every day
since April 15. Bullion futures for June delivery traded at
$1,504.30 an ounce, near a record $1,506.50.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Kyoungwha Kim at 
 kkim19@bloomberg.net  